        "id": 4685,
        "name": "Alex Miller",
        "username": "alexmiller",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/alexmiller/{size}/326_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-07-19T02:26:53.342Z",
        "cooked": "<p><code>--locality_zoneid</code> is what most of the policy logic goes off of, so it is the correct one to set.</p>\n<p>Setting zoneid to be a datacenter would let you use <code>triple</code> to spread data across three or more datacenter and synchronously commit to all of them.  Your data would only be in three random datacenters, and if you have less than three datacenters, FDB will be unavailable.</p>\n<p>I don\u2019t think you\u2019d gain anything by doing this over using one of the modes more meant for multi-dc replication.</p>",
        "post_number": 4,
